<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Basilica_della_Santa_Casa" title="Basilica della Santa Casa">Basilica della Santa Casa</a></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Nicholas_Russo&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Notes"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="reflist reflist-lower-alpha">
<div class="mw-references-wrap"><ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-birthplace-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-birthplace_3-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Several sources list his birthplace as <a href="/wiki/Ascoli_Satriano" title="Ascoli Satriano">Ascoli Satriano</a>, in the <a href="/wiki/Apulia" title="Apulia">Apulia</a> region of southern Italy.<sup id="cite_ref-:1_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:1-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-:14_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:14-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-operarius-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-operarius_18-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">An <span title="Latin-language text"><i lang="la">operarius</i></span> is a Jesuit who works as a priest away from his Jesuit community.<sup id="cite_ref-gramatowski20_17-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gramatowski20-17">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
